  <name>Module 2</name>
  <summary>&lt;p style="text-align: right;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id="docs-internal-guid-d694433d-7b54-d161-9565-cafcf04961e6" style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;a href="@@PLUGINFILE@@/m2.png" title="Display larger image"&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/m2.png" width="450" height="527" alt="Graphic displays the four units that make up Module 2, Integrating Digital Literacy Into Adult English Language Instruction. Unit 1 is Digital Literacy in Our Lives. Units 2 through 4 build on Unit 1 and can be taken in any order of interest: Unit 2, Information and Communication Technologies for Language Learning; Unit 3, Digital Information Literacy; and Unit 4, Solving Problems in Technology-Rich Environments. Participants can choose to complete as many units as necessary.  " style="float: right; margin: 5px;" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id="docs-internal-guid-d694433d-7b54-d161-9565-cafcf04961e6" style="font-size: medium;"&gt;The module is designed for teachers and administrators interested in integrating digital literacy in their adult English Language Acquisition (previously referred to as ESL) classes and programs.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;This module contains 4 units. Estimated completion time for each unit is 2-3 hours.  A certificate can be earned for each unit upon completion of the unit activities. &lt;span&gt;T&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;here are additional materials within the units that provide for deeper learning opportunities.  These optional deeper learning opportunities will take time beyond the estimated 2-3 hours for completion.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Review the Module 2 Introduction to begin.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
